				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Cithen the Bard...<a name="74753"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 23 05 6:29 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>My advice to you at this low a lvl is to manually twist. 
<br />

<br />
ie Start first song
<br />
   Wait for it to land
<br />
   Click it once to stop it
<br />
   start second song
<br />
   Wait for it to land ( Almost all Bard songs are 3 sec cast, so
<br />
                                              1-1000, 2-1000, 3-1000 click)
<br />
   Click it once to stop it
<br />
   Start third song
<br />
   Wait for it to land
<br />
   click it once to stop it
<br />

<br />
Then go back to first song.
<br />

<br />
I have 3 reasons for suggesting this.
<br />

<br />
1&gt; At your Lvl your skills are not that well developed and you will fizzle a LOT.  When this happens, just click the song you fizzled on ONCE to get it going.  You will lose a little time, but it doesn't matter as much as you think
<br />

<br />
2&gt; You will learn your songs better by twisting this way.
<br />

<br />
3&gt; You can change your twist at will.
<br />

<br />
It sounds to me like you are trying to use a Macro in your Hotkeys to twist, and you would need to put some /pause ## 's into it.  Pauses work wierdly in macros, and are hard to set up for just one Song/Spell, doing 3 in a Macro is gonna be a lot tougher.  Basic reason is LAG.
<br />

<br />
You can use the new /melody #1 #2 #3, but I think at this lvl, with Fizzles being so hi and the strange way Melody has been changed this will not be appropriate for you.
<br />

<br />
What I did was set up like 3 or 4different hotkey banks for different things.  I made some buttons stay the same on each ie Attack, Sit, /ASSIST and dragged my Selos, Heal, and Snare to the same one on each.  Then on each one I dragged different songs that were specific to that Hotkey Bank to where they were right beside each other so I could twist 3 manually in the Hotkey Bank but had heal for between fights, Selos for get out of dodge, and Snare .. well.. just because.  Then when you get an upgrade you can put the upgrade song in the same spot as the one before, and your Hotkeys will remain the same.
<br />

<br />
Just my feelings from a 56th Lvl Bard....</span></td>
